{{Infobox software | name = Bicom Systems | developer = Bicom Systems | released = {{Start date and age|2004}} | latest release date = {{Start date and age|mf=yes|2018|03|17}} | latest release version = Version 5.1 | programming language = [[C++]] | operating system = [[Microsoft Windows]], [[OS X]], [[Linux]], [[iOS]], [[Android OS]] | genre = [[Voice over Internet Protocol]] | license = [[Proprietary software|Proprietary]] | website = {{URL|www.bicomsystems.com}} }}
'''Bicom Systems''' is a producer and vendor of [[Asterisk (PBX)]]-based [[unified communications]] solutions for VoIP businesses. Bicom Systems uses open standards telephony to create proprietary turnkey solutions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wholesale-voip.tmcnet.com/articles/353672-voip-innovations-partners-with-bicom-systems-icon-voice.htm|title=Wholesale VoIP - VoIP Innovations Partners with Bicom Systems and ICON Voice Networks|first=VoIP|last=Innovations|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.voipinnovations.com/blog/index.php/thanks-to-interoperability-testing-we-have-new-partners|title=Thanks to Interoperability Testing, We Have New Partners|first=Natalie|last=DeCario|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2016}}</ref> Products include all of the software and hardware components involved in building a [[VoIP]] business or [[ITSP]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.voipreview.org/reviews/bicom|title=Bicom - 0 Reviews - voipreview.org|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2016}}</ref>
==History== Bicom Systems began researching and creating telecoms management software in 2003.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telecomreseller.com/2015/02/07/bicom-systems-introduces-new-keysystem/|title=Bicom Systems introduces new KeySystem|date=7 February 2015|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2016}}</ref> An Asterisk pioneer,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ipphonesresource.com/articles/417468-bicom-tells-its-telephony-story.htm|title=Bicom Tells Its Telephony Story|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2016}}</ref> Bicom Systems launched the first ever open standards turnkey telephony system in 2004.
Bicom Systems made its first public trade exhibition at ITEXPO in January 2016 to launch new products. They will be attending Astricon in September 2016 to showcase their complete solution.<ref>http://www.asterisk.org/community/astricon-user-conference/exhibitor-list</ref>
Bicom Systems has seven products<ref>{{cite web|url=http://itexpo.tmcnet.com/west/shownews/articles/416544-bicom-systems-unveils-new-ip-key-systems-solution.htm|title=Bicom Systems Unveils New IP Key Systems Solution at ITEXPO|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2016}}</ref> including a desktop and mobile softphone,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.channelpartnersonline.com/news/2016/03/bicom-systems-releases-glocom-go-mobile-softphone.aspx|title=Bicom Systems Releases gloCOM GO Mobile Softphone|date=18 March 2016|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2016}}</ref> an IP PBX telephony platform,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.channelpartnersonline.com/news/2016/03/bicom-systems-releases-pbxware-version-4-0.aspx|title=Bicom Systems Releases PBXware Version 4.0|date=17 March 2016|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2016}}</ref> and an IP Key Systems product.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.channelpartnersonline.com/news/2016/03/bicom-systems-intros-ip-key-systems.aspx|title=Bicom Systems Intros IP Key Systems|date=16 March 2016|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2016}}</ref> Supported hardware manufacturers include [[Polycom]], Yealink,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yealink.com/News_info.aspx?NewsId=49&CateId=213|title=Yealink - UC＆C terminal, video collaboration, conference phone, IP phone|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cloudcommunications.com/yealink-t2x-telephones-are-now-fully-compatible-with-bicom-systems/|title=Yealink T2X Telephones Are Now Fully Compatible with Bicom Systems - Cloud Communications Alliance|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2016}}</ref> and others.
