'''Braulio Medel Cámara''' (born 1947 in [[Seville]], [[Spain]]). Chairman of '''Unicaja''', a financial institution that holds 1.5% of the equity capital of [[Iberdrola]]. He has a Doctorate in [[Economic Sciences]] and [[Business Studies]] from [[Universidad Complutense de Madrid]] and is Professor of [[Public Finance]] at the University of Malaga.

==Career==
Since 1991, Medel Cámara has been Chairman of Unicaja.{{citation needed|date=July 2015}} He is also Chairman of the Federation of Savings Banks of [[Andalusia]],{{citation needed|date=July 2015}} and Vice-Chairman of the Spanish Confederation of Savings Banks, where he held the post of Chairman until 1998.{{citation needed|date=July 2015}}

Model Cámara is the [[Junta de Andalucía]] Undersecretary of the Economy and Finance.{{citation needed|date=July 2015}} He has published over a hundred or so scientific works, counting books and articles in specialised journals.{{citation needed|date=July 2015}} He has been the Chairman of the Iberdrola Advisory Council in Andalusia since its establishment in November 2004.{{citation needed|date=July 2015}}

==Fraud charges==
In 2014, Medel Cámara was charged with fraud in a still developing criminal case. The charges were about a supposed fraud of 117 million euros.<ref>http://politica.elpais.com/politica/2014/05/14/actualidad/1400103941_388017.html</ref><ref>http://www.elconfidencial.com/espana/2014-06-04/la-imputacion-formal-de-braulio-medel-en-los-ere-le-obligara-a-dejar-unicaja_141226/</ref><ref>http://sevilla.abc.es/andalucia/20140514/sevi-alaya-imputa-medel-201405141916.html</ref>

